  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Gill's Exposition of the Entire Bible",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Whosoever doth not bear his cross,.... All reproach, afflictions, persecutions, and death itself, cheerfully and patiently; the Ethiopic version renders it, \"of his death the cross\"; it signifies whatever is trying and disagreeable to flesh and blood: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "and come after me; bearing his cross; as Christ himself was about to do, and which doubtless he had in view; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "cannot be my disciple; he is not so in reality, nor does he deserve the name. ",
        "children": [
